Judge Fitzgerald: Knowing
everything you know about him,

26:45.604 --> 26:47.780
you're sure you want
to keep your attorney?

26:47.823 --> 26:51.784
♪♪

26:51.827 --> 26:55.135
With everything I know
about him, yes.

26:55.178 --> 26:56.789
♪♪

26:56.832 --> 26:59.008
I was looking right at Rufus
when he got shot down.

26:59.052 --> 27:01.315
Who shot him?
The cops.

27:01.358 --> 27:04.492
How did that
make you feel?

27:04.535 --> 27:06.929
Scared for my life.

27:06.973 --> 27:10.367
What did you do?

27:10.411 --> 27:11.978
I ran.

27:12.021 --> 27:14.589
What did you think would happen
if you didn't run?

27:18.419 --> 27:20.160
I thought
it would be me next.

27:22.249 --> 27:25.600
How did you feel about
Michael Rossi?

27:32.781 --> 27:36.002
You know, I'm deeply sorry
for his family, honestly,

27:36.045 --> 27:38.744
from the bottom of my heart,
but I just --

27:42.095 --> 27:45.098
I don't know
how we got here.

27:45.141 --> 27:46.969
When you were down
that dead-end street

27:47.013 --> 27:50.407
and he came to arrest you --
we all want to know,

27:50.451 --> 27:56.413
and the jury needs to hear --
what was in your mind?

27:59.329 --> 28:02.419
Wasn't in my mind.

28:02.463 --> 28:05.118
Deeper than that.

28:05.161 --> 28:07.555
In that moment, in my bones,

28:07.598 --> 28:09.209
it's just that thing
that everybody know --

28:09.252 --> 28:12.734
If a cop come for you
and a cop get ahold of you?

28:12.778 --> 28:14.475
You could die.

28:14.518 --> 28:16.651
So what did you do?

28:16.695 --> 28:18.827
[Breathes deeply]

28:18.871 --> 28:19.480
There was, like,
cages with these, uh,

28:19.523 --> 28:22.048
[Breathes deeply]

28:22.091 --> 28:28.010
containers at the end,
and, uh, the only way out

28:28.054 --> 28:29.969
I could see
was over the containers.

28:30.012 --> 28:32.580
And he was
between me and that.

28:32.623 --> 28:34.669
And then, uh --

28:34.713 --> 28:38.412
And then I --
I tried to get over there.

28:38.455 --> 28:40.631
Stop!
And, uh...

28:40.675 --> 28:42.242
♪♪

28:42.285 --> 28:45.158
...he stepped across to --
to block my path.

28:45.201 --> 28:48.422
It's over.And...

28:48.465 --> 28:50.990
It's over.

28:51.033 --> 28:52.992
There was, uh,
some sh-shoulder-to-sh--

28:53.035 --> 28:54.776
There was
some shoulder contact.

28:54.820 --> 28:57.300
Shoulder-to-shoulder contact?

28:57.344 --> 28:59.607
♪♪

28:59.650 --> 29:00.739
[Thud]

29:00.782 --> 29:02.349
He fell back.[Rossi wailing]

29:02.392 --> 29:05.308
Hit his -- Hit his head.

29:05.352 --> 29:09.791
His back of his head hit --
hit the iron bar in --

29:09.835 --> 29:11.358
in the ground,
and there was...

29:11.401 --> 29:12.881
Moses: Breathe!
Come on, breathe!

29:12.925 --> 29:13.926
...there was all this blood
all of a sudden, and...

29:13.969 --> 29:15.057
Moses: Breathe!
Come on, breathe!

29:15.101 --> 29:17.320
Yo! Breathe!
Hey, stay with me, man!

29:17.364 --> 29:19.627
Stay with me!

29:19.670 --> 29:22.238
What happened when
the second police officer

29:22.282 --> 29:23.544
arrived on the scene?

29:23.587 --> 29:25.111
What happened when
the second police officer

29:25.154 --> 29:26.634
He took a shot at me.

29:26.677 --> 29:28.941
Had you shown any aggressive
intent toward him?

29:28.984 --> 29:32.683
No, I-I was running away,
and I had my back turned to him.

29:32.727 --> 29:34.381
♪♪

29:34.424 --> 29:37.123
He shot at your back?

29:37.166 --> 29:38.646
What did that tell you?

29:38.689 --> 29:40.779
That he was trying to kill me

29:40.822 --> 29:42.824
and that I was right
to run away

29:42.868 --> 29:46.262
and I-I was right
to protect myself.

29:46.306 --> 29:47.394
Thank you.

29:47.437 --> 29:47.916
and I-I was right
to protect myself.

29:47.960 --> 29:49.048
♪♪

29:49.091 --> 29:49.918
and I-I was right
to protect myself.

29:54.836 --> 29:57.273
This won't take long.

29:57.317 --> 29:58.013
When the police arrived
on the corner,

29:58.057 --> 29:58.927
This won't take long.

29:58.971 --> 29:59.667
did you know
they were cops?

29:59.710 --> 30:00.755
This won't take long.

30:00.799 --> 30:02.104
Yeah.

30:02.148 --> 30:03.584
Mm-hmm. And when you ran
from the corner,

30:03.627 --> 30:05.194
it was to
escape police officers?

30:05.238 --> 30:07.588
Yes.
And down
that dead-end street,

30:07.631 --> 30:08.894
nothing had changed?

30:08.937 --> 30:10.417
How do you mean?

30:10.460 --> 30:11.679
You knew Michael Rossi
was a police officer.

30:11.722 --> 30:13.594
You knew he wanted
to arrest you.

30:13.637 --> 30:15.335
Yes.

30:15.378 --> 30:17.163
Did he draw his weapon?

30:17.206 --> 30:18.773
No.

30:18.817 --> 30:22.168
Did he make
any aggressive move toward you?

30:22.211 --> 30:23.865
He was a cop.

30:23.909 --> 30:26.520
What else did you know about
Michael Rossi in that moment?

30:28.043 --> 30:29.740
Nothing.

30:29.784 --> 30:32.265
You didn't know he had
an exemplary service record?

30:32.308 --> 30:35.181
You didn't know he had a wife
and five small children,

30:35.224 --> 30:37.792
or where he was born,
or how much he loved baseball?

30:37.836 --> 30:39.881
No.What does this have to do
with anything?

30:39.925 --> 30:41.752
You made an assumption
based on the one thing
you knew about him.

30:41.796 --> 30:42.884
That he was a cop.

30:42.928 --> 30:44.886
What?
What does that make you?

30:48.107 --> 30:50.979
You -- You just don't get it,
lady.

30:51.023 --> 30:52.024
I mean, how could you?Judge Fitzpatrick: Mr. Johnson.

30:52.067 --> 30:53.242
You -- You just don't get it,
lady.

30:53.286 --> 30:54.765
No, no, no. She just
gonna ask me a question

30:54.809 --> 30:56.593
and just get to sit down?

30:56.637 --> 30:59.031
No. The way I was raised --
That's called rude.

30:59.074 --> 31:01.207
Mr. Johnson.No, man, that's not right.

31:01.250 --> 31:04.732
Your Honor,
I'm entitled to redirect.

31:04.775 --> 31:06.777
Would you like to continue
with what you were saying?

31:06.821 --> 31:08.518
Yes.
Please continue.

31:08.562 --> 31:09.693
She's talking
about assumptions.

31:09.737 --> 31:10.651
She don't know nothing
about me.

31:10.694 --> 31:11.870
She's talking
about assumptions.

31:11.913 --> 31:13.480
You making assumptions
that I'm one of these

31:13.523 --> 31:15.047
little hood rats
on the corner.

31:15.090 --> 31:17.223
That's not me.
Every day, I train.

31:17.266 --> 31:19.790
Every day, I train my butt off
to get where I'm trying to go.

31:19.834 --> 31:22.793
And you talking about that
I'm making assumptions.

31:22.837 --> 31:25.318
I have never been in trouble
a day in my life.

31:25.361 --> 31:26.928
You can ask everybody.
Everybody know me.

31:26.972 --> 31:28.538
Everybody know
I stay out the way.

31:28.582 --> 31:30.453
And you can ask everybody
where I'm from --

31:30.497 --> 31:33.500
Everybody know we talk
about the same thing about cops.

31:33.543 --> 31:35.241
The world has given cops
the permission to --

31:35.284 --> 31:37.765
to -- to -- to hurt us,
to kill us,

31:37.808 --> 31:40.246
and there's
no repercussions at all.

31:40.289 --> 31:43.249
And if you -- And if you manage
to get out of there alive,

31:43.292 --> 31:46.992
they will always be believed,
they will always be the truth.

31:47.035 --> 31:50.996
We will always be the liars.

